# GUIDED PROBLEM SOLVING

---

GP1) The sailboat traveled a total of ½ mile in ¼ hour.


--


i) Write an equation that represents the relationship between the total miles traveled, $y$, in $x$ hours.

 $y$ miles per $x$ hours


--

 $\frac{1}{2}$ mile per $\frac{1}{4}$ hour


--
$\downarrow \times 4 \hspace{2.5em} \downarrow \times 4$


--
 $2$ miles per $1$ hour


--

$k=2$


--
$y = 2x$

--
$\hspace{3em} k = \frac{y}{x}$

--
$= \frac{\frac{1}{2}}{\frac{1}{4}}$

--
$= \frac{1}{2} \div \frac{1}{4}$

--
$= \frac{1}{2} \cdot \frac{4}{1}$

--
$ = 2$




---

ii) Use the equation to determine how long it will take the boat to travel 1 mile.

$y = 1 \text{ mile}$

--

$y = 2 x$


--
$1 = 2x$


--
$x=\frac{1}{2} \text{ hour}$

---


iii) Use a constant of proportionality (unit rate) to determine how long it will take the sailboat to travel 1 mile.


 $\frac{1}{4}$ hour per $\frac{1}{2}$ mile


--
$\downarrow \times 2 \hspace{2.5em} \downarrow \times 2$


--
 $\frac{1}{2}$ hour per $1$ mile


