.medium[
GP3) It took one scholar 30 minutes to read $\frac{2}{5}$ of the assignment.

i) Write an equation that represents the relationship between the amount of the assignment read, $y$, in $x$ hours.
]


--

 $y$ assignments per $x$ hours


--

 $\frac{2}{5}$ assignment per $\frac{1}{2}$ hour


--
$\downarrow \times 2 \hspace{5.25em} \downarrow \times 2$


--
 $\frac{4}{5}$ assignment per $1$ hour


--

$k=\frac{4}{5}$


--
$y = \frac{4}{5}x$

--
$\hspace{3em} k = \frac{y}{x}$

--
$= \frac{\frac{2}{5}}{\frac{1}{2}}$

--
$= \frac{2}{5} \div \frac{1}{2}$

--
$= \frac{2}{5} \cdot \frac{2}{1}$

--
$ = \frac{4}{5}$





